This file describes some subtlties about the build process


MAKEFILE (make Makefile  of  resources/build_make.sh)

The makefile of the project is split in two parts, the first is in
Makefile, it is generated by coq_makefile (and patched by
resources/patchmake.sh). The second describes how to build the
documentation the way we want, it is in resources/MoreMakefile and is
called from the first one.

"resources/patchmake.sh Makefile" performs several operations on the
Makefile produced by coq_makefile:
1) add the line "resources/patchmake.sh Makefile" to the "Makefile"
   target. "make Makefile" will therefore re-patch Makefile.
2) removes all documentation related targets
2) add "-include resources/MoreMakefile" at the end.

"resources/build_make.sh" (must be called from the main directory)
builds a Makefile from file _CoqProject.

If you add, rename or removed files, you should

1) modify the content of file _CoqProject accordingly
2) do "make Makefile" or "resources/build_make.sh"
3) make ; make alldoc should work again.


DOCUMENTATION (make alldoc)

 PDF (make pdf/xxx.pdf)

The file resources/CoursDeLogique-nfp120.tex is a preamble to all
latex files produced by coqdoc. It contains the standard preamble +
some utf8 definitions. We use the standard coqdoc.sty but this may
change at some point.

 HTML (make html)

We use our own coqdoc.css (resources/tools/coqdoc/coqdoc.css).


